main event: A witness observed a large, round, metallic object with a soft glow hovering over a field in Alto, Tennessee on April 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object was approximately 50-60 feet in diameter and hovered over a field for several minutes before rapidly accelerating and disappearing.
The witness, a local resident, observed the object for 10-15 minutes from their vehicle.
The incident was investigated by the U.S. Air Force as part of Project Blue Book and was classified as an Unidentified Flying Object.
On April 13, 1966, two other witnesses in Alto, Tennessee reported seeing a luminous, pulsing, white object moving in a straight line from north to south.
The report includes photographs of the original sighting location, a rural landscape with a field and distant structure or landmark.
sighted object: a large, round, metallic object with a soft glow
photographs: yes, the report includes photographs of the sighting location
